'''Homostatic''' :quality of two or more objects being in the same state

Example: 

'''Homostatic repulsion''': describes any occurrence of [[repulsion]] which can exist at the fundamental level. Refers to the state of mutual repulsion between all particles that are in the same electric state or have the same magnetic orientation (two electrons, two positrons, etc.), as well as magnetostatic fields that are in parallel orientation.
